<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-12T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-12T12:00:00-05:00" n="887" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/549: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-12T20:00:00+03:00">June 12,
                                    1942—8 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 13—1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>585. I have just learned unofficially that the fourth Liberator, referred
                            to in my 581, June 12, landed about noon today at Diyarbekir.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Cairo.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>